If you’re wondering how my Christmas shopping is going…

It’s not! 😆😭🫣

I’m definitely more of a last minute shopper, so the one-stop-shop is a MUST

@locallexmarket is such a hidden gem for all the local gifts 🎁 🙌

I was blown away by the options they had for literally everyone on my list—from kids and pets, to friends, parents, and even men (we all know they’re are the hardest to buy for!) 

Local Lex Market sells goods from over 80 different Kentucky local businesses all in one shop. If you haven’t checked out all that @locallexmarket has to offer, NOW is the time!

Are you a last minute shopper like me or are you finished with your holiday shopping?

Get your weekend brunch on at @maplestreetbiscuitcompany 😋

I got to check out Lexington’s newest biscuit restaurant, Maple Street Biscuit Company at their grand opening this week and y’all I was blown away! 

The delicious food, handmade biscuits, and good ol’ southern hospitality you’ll find here are a welcome addition in town! 

WHAT WE ATE: 

🐔The Squawking Goat 
a chicken biscuit featuring goat cheese medallions and house made pepper jam 

🍳 Sausage Frittaffle 
eggs, cheese, and sausage omelet made in the waffle maker 

🧇 Little Grace Waffles 
the kids meal version of their chocolate chip waffles, topped with strawberries and whipped cream

🍄Shiitake Mushroom Gravy & Biscuits 
I am a biscuits and gravy person and I’ll be honest, I wasn’t sure I’d like the mushroom gravy but it was SO GOOD! 

Of course I couldn’t leave without grabbing a half dozen of their iced cinnamon biscuits to bring home

Maple Street has such a fun menu and everything I tried was delicious—I can’t wait to go back soon and try more!

✨Tag a friend you want to go with in the comments ✨

Easiest “Fun Mom” meal ever 🍕😋 

Luke has been traveling a lot for work lately, so when it’s just me and the kids at home we try to make things fun! 

That’s why I always keep a pizza in the freezer and @urbanpiepizzaco is our favorite! 

Not only is Urban Pie insanely delicious, but each of their pizzas are made with premium quality ingredients that I can feel good about serving to my kids.

Since it’s #NationalSauceMonth I grabbed the Pesto Mozzerella pizza and classic Pepperoni pizza featuring their signature Creamy Rosa sauce (marinara & Alfredo blend 🤤) 

Grab one of Urban Pie’s unique and tasty pizzas on your next @wholefoods run! 

Which slice are you choosing, pesto or pepperoni?

Let this be your sign! 🏔️☀️

We used to think we couldn’t go hiking with our kids. “They won’t be able to keep up, they’ll just complain the whole time, it won’t be fun for anyone.”

But we were WRONG! 

Sure, maybe we have to go a little slower, and snacks are a MUST…

but hiking with our kids is the best experience and we’ve made so many great memories while exploring nature together! 

📍Red Rocks Amphitheater 

#ShareLexKy #denvercolorado #hikecolorado #redrocksamphitheater #redrockstatepark #hikewithkids #familyhike #getoutsideandexplore #hikingwithkids #travelfamily

Our adventures in Colorado have come to a close and the Gifford crew is officially back in Kentucky! 

We had so much fun hiking and exploring one of our favorite places for the first time as a family 

One of the coolest things about supporting local is that you can do it from literally anywhere 🌎 The best way to experience any city is by checking out their local business scene! 

The Denver area has such a great local vibe and so many amazing small businesses to support 🙌

I’ll be sharing some local Colorado content from our trip—and maybe even some long-term Airbnb/traveling with kids stuff if y’all would like to see that too, let me know in the comments! 

Where is your favorite place (in the US) to travel? ✈️ 

#ShareLexKy #travellocal #visitdenver #hikecolorado #visitcolorado #travelfamily #familytravelblogger #explorelocal #smallbizlove

When your kids are too young to make you breakfast in bed, you head to @thefreshmarket #TheFreshMarketPartner 

I let them do the shopping and honestly, my kids really know me well—I’m very proud! 

They picked out my favorite chocolate chip muffins, broccoli cheddar quiche, orange juice, fresh berries, and of course a beautiful bouquet of fresh flowers for a lovely Mother’s Day brunch at home✨

The Fresh Market makes it so simple to celebrate all the Moms in your life with their great selection of delicious treats, easy to serve meals, gifts, flowers & more! 

The best gift of all is time spent together 💛

#CelebrateMom #MothersDay #MothersDayBrunch #ShareLexKY #sharethelex #KentuckyMom #LocalMom #BrunchIdeas #TheFreshMarket

My favorite kind of festivals are strawberry festivals 🍓

@eckertsorchard is hosting their annual Strawberry Festival THIS WEEKEND Saturday & Sunday from 10am-5pm! 

Take the beautiful backroad drive out to Versailles and enjoy you-pick strawberries, fun for the kids, live music, and food trucks on site! 

And if picking your own berries doesn’t sound like fun to you, they have plenty available in their country store, along with cider, jam, gifts, and more. 

Picking strawberries at Eckert’s is a tradition my kids and I look forward to every single year and we could spend all day having fun at the farm! 

✨Tag a friend you want to go with in the comments and I’ll send a lucky winner passes for the day of your choice! ✨
——giveaway is now closed——

Now excuse me while I go make dessert with these gorgeous strawberries 😍

#ShareLexKY #EckertsOrchard #StrawberryPicking #FreshStrawaberries #ShareTheLex #SupportLocalFarms #KentuckyProud #KentuckyMom

Eating this strawberry yogurt parfait and pretending I’m somewhere fancy 🍓✨

The key to this easy summer breakfast/snack perfection is fresh fruit and @sweetgrassgranola 👌😋

Sweet Grass Southern Granola is made with Kentucky Sorghum Cane Syrup, Kentucky Chia Seeds, and Appalachian Sea Salt for a delicious @kentuckyproud local snack! 

MAKE YOUR PARFAIT:

🫙Grab the cutest glass you have
🫐Add fresh fruit of your choice and a sprinkle of granola to the bottom 
🥛Layer with yogurt and more fruit & granola 
🍓Add one more layer of yogurt and top with as much fruit and @sweetgrassgranola as you want! 

This will be on repeat for me all summer, y’all! You can grab @sweetgrassgranola (I used the Cherry Home Companion flavor here) at @lexfarmmkt or on their website! 

#ShareLexKy #SweetGrassGranola #KentuckyProud #EatLocal #ShareTheLex #KentuckyMade #LocalEats #LocalFoods #granolagirl #granolabowl #granolarecipe #yogurtparfait #kentuckygram

Checked out the new @sharetealexington on Richmond Rd last night!🧋🙌

They just opened this week and were the perfect stop after my solo-grocery run to Kroger (I don’t care what anyone says, going grocery shopping alone IS self-care!) 

@sharetealexington is offering 20% off your order if you follow them on Facebook or Instagram, so definitely give them a follow before you stop in! 

I got the mango green milk tea with boba at half sweetness level which was perfect for me since I don’t like sweet drinks. They have a good variety to choose from with hot, iced, and blended drinks, service was great and super fast, and they’re open until 9pm! 

✨Share this with a boba tea loving friend! ✨

#sharelexky #sharethelex #kentuckygram #lexingtonky #lexingtonfoodie #bobatea #sharetea

My very first use of 🐝 venom as an alternative to Botox 💉

I found @wildflowerapothecaryma on instagram not too long ago and was immediately interested in trying her products! I love finding small businesses to support and natural alternatives that give real results ✨

I have ZERO judgment for anyone who gets Botox, I’ve considered it so many times but wanted to try some natural alternatives first and I’m so glad I found this one! 

The fact that this product minimized the appearance of lines and movement in my forehead after MINUTES is insane to me! Can’t wait to see the results I get after using regularly 🙌

Comment “link please!” and I will DM you with the link 

Would you try this alternative to Botox?

It’s not everyday a burger looks as good as it tastes 😋🍔

I’ve seen Timmy Two Times shared on Facebook a lot lately with people saying it’s “the best burger in town” so of course I had to check it out! 

Y’all this hidden gem lives up to the hype! Tucked in the Keithshire Place shopping center off Clays Mill Rd, Timmy Two Times is the hole in the wall we’ve all been searching for. 

Their burger and side of fries starts at $10 and both are absolutely delicious—I’m super picky about fries and these are SO good 🤤

Every sandwich on their small but mighty menu comes with your choice of fries, tater tots, egg rolls, or chicken taquitos…

The important question is, which side are you choosing?? 

#ShareLexKy #ShareTheLex #EatLocal #BurgerJoint #localburger #localrestaurant

Motherhood is dangerous. 

It simultaneously opens you up to the greatest joy and pain imaginable, the most valuable additions to your life, or the deepest losses.

Today I got real vulnerable on substack and shared not only about this powerful book, Dangerous Hope, by local author @britt_ross108 but also about my own experience of pregnancy loss. 

Britt’s book has been on my heart to share with y’all since she released it back around Christmas, but I’ll be honest I was scared to share on socials because I knew I couldn’t talk about how important her story is without sharing my own story too.

I have never felt so seen in my experience becoming a mom as I did when reading Dangerous Hope. Brittany has a way of writing to the deepest parts of you and letting women who have also gone through loss know they didn’t go there alone. 

It’s a story of hope, healing, and empowerment that I believe all women would be encouraged by. 

Go read the post I shared over on substack (link in my bio) and grab a copy of Brittany’s book for you or a friend 📚

On top of being a local author, @britt_ross108 is also the founder of a local nonprofit @mission108 that supports anti-human trafficking efforts and funds a safe house for young girls in India.

I know this isn’t my usual content and I really appreciate your support 💛

#ShareLexKy #DangerousHope #LocalAuthor #ShareTheLex #PregnancyLoss #BookReview

It’s BURGER WEEK 🍔
but you already knew that! 

I got to try @campus.pub special for @lexingtonburgerweek and it was SO good! 

The Kevin Smashburger features two smash burger patties topped with American cheese, onion purée and special burger sauce—AND it comes with their house made kettle chips, all for $7! This was the perfect classic smashburger 😋

Campus Pub just released all new food and drink menus and you’ll want to try soon! 

What Burger Week specials have you tried so far??

@thelextheatreco 

“The hills are alive” as The Lexington Theatre Company brings this Rogers & Hammerstein classic to life right here in the bluegrass THIS WEEKEND ONLY!! 

I am always impressed with @thelextheatreco but I was blown away with this cast and performance! ❤️

You’ll want to hum along with Maria and the Von Trapp family as they perform these classic tunes accompanied by The Lexington Theatre Company’s live orchestra! 

You can still grab tickets for their remaining shows: 
July 14 7:30pm

blackberry picking vibes ✨

We had so much fun out at @eckertsorchard for their blackberry festival yesterday! And the fun is still going today with u-pick blackberries, live music, food trucks, and TONS of activities for the kids! 

When I tell you our experience yesterday was incredible, I mean it was PURE MAGIC ✨ 

Rows and rows of bushes filled to the brim with juicy blackberries, ripe for the picking—and we all enjoyed picking them! 

I went through my photos and felt like we had just stepped off of a photo shoot in the Italian countryside 😍 There is something so beautiful about these lush canopies of berries that I just can’t get over! 

We spent a perfect summer afternoon out at @eckertsorchard and I highly recommend experiencing this magic for yourself! 

Am I crazy? Please tell me I’m not alone in my fruit picking obsession 😂 

#ShareLexKy #EckertsOrchard #KentuckyProud #LookAtLexington #ShareTheLex #BlackberryPicking

@thelextheatreco presents MEMPHIS🎶✨

As always, this is a show you won’t want to miss!! The Lexington Theatre Company continues to blow me away with their incredible performances and Memphis is no exception! 

In this Tony-winning Broadway hit, you’ll watch as Huey and Felicia fall in love on stage, navigate the struggles of life in 1950s Memphis, and bring to life rock-n-roll! 

There is no reason to travel for Broadway-quality musical theater when The Lex brings it to us right here in downtown Lexington! 

Be sure to catch one of their FIVE performances this weekend at the Lexington Opera House 
August 3-4 at 7:30pm 
August 5 at 1:00pm & 7:30pm
August 6 at 1:00pm 

Get your tickets now! (Link in bio) 

#ShareLexKy #TheLexingtonTheatreCompany #TheLex #LookAtLexington #MemphisLex #LexFam #MusicalsMakeLifeBetter #MusicalTheatre

Day date ft.  @thelextheatreco ✨

Luke and I went to see Memphis this afternoon and y’all I hope you made one of this weekend’s performances because it was incredible!! 

I’m a total sucker for the charm of @lexoperahouse and literally anything The Lexington Theatre Company performs—I refuse to get over how magical their shows are! 

There is just something about getting dressed up, heading downtown (with my handsome man 😍) and watching top quality musical theatre that gets me every time 

Already can’t wait to go back again for White Christmas! ❄️ 

#ShareLexKy #LookAtLexington #ShareTheLex #TheLexingtonTheatreCompany #TheLex #MusicalsMakeLifeBetter

My kind of ✨girl dinner✨

I got to try all of these delicious slices of @__cakesbycoco cake recently and they were all so delicious! Cake boards should really be a thing, don’t you think?! 🍰

Flavors shown: chocolate, classic white, pistachio, & funfetti

Which flavor would you try first?

The Woodland Art Fair is this weekend!! 

This amazing event, put on by @lexingtonartleague is a summer highlight here in Lexington, and thousands make their way through Woodland Park every year to shop from local artists and makers! 

If you’re heading to this year’s art fair, here are some more local businesses just across the street in the Woodland Triangle you won’t want to miss while you’re there! 

It’s a beautiful weekend to get outside and #shoplocal 

Image credit: @lexingtonartleague 

#ShareLexKy #LookAtLexington #ShareTheLex #LexingtonArtLeague #WoodlandArtFair

One of the easiest ways to shop local is by going to the farmers’ market! 🍅🥬🌽 #ad 

I personally love the Saturday morning market in downtown Lexington and there are so many local farmers & makers to buy from, but did you know Lexington has a handful of other local farmers’ markets throughout the week? 

Head to my stories or click the link in my bio to find all the @kentuckyproud farmers’ markets near you! 

While at @lexfarmmkt this week I got everything I needed to make this delicious EBLT 🤤 if you’ve been here a while you probably know how much I love a good egg sandwich and this one was next level!

Which local farmers’ market is your go-to? 

#KentuckyProud #KYProud #ShareLexKy

Apple season > all other seasons 🍎

We spent an afternoon at @eckertsorchard picking apples, getting lost in the corn maze, and having so much fun! 

It’s officially looking like fall here in the bluegrass & apple picking is the perfect activity to kick off the fall season! 

We were pleasantly surprised to find the corn maze open and enjoyed sipping a delicious cider slushee while we wandered the maze 😋 

Fall is THE season to head to @eckertsorchard for apple picking, farm fun & even private bonfires! Not to mention pick your own pumpkins start this weekend! 🎃

Are you team apples or pumpkins??

#ShareLexKy #ShareTheLex #LookAtLexington #EckertsOrchard #KentuckyProud

Send this to your Gilmore Girls obsessed friend! 🍂🍁

This adorable coffee & local gift shop is bringing all the Stars Hollow vibes ✨ They even have Gilmore Girls playing in the store nonstop! 

Grab a friend, put on your favorite sweater, and head to @theamsden for a cup of coffee and stroll around this adorable Kentucky small town for a perfect fall day 🎃🍂🍁

The only question is, are you drinking a pumpkin spice or an apple cider?

Fall is my favorite time to visit a @kentuckyproud farm! #ad 

There is something so magical about heading out to the pumpkin patch, searching for the perfect pumpkin, listening to my kids talk about what their going to paint or carve, sipping warm apple cider, and soaking up the Kentucky fall weather together! 

And of course getting lost in the corn maze! 🌽 @devinescornmaze is THE BEST corn maze in Kentucky—they’ve even been featured in @usatoday 

Don’t forget to take a wagon ride out to the pumpkin patch and pick your free pumpkin! 🎃 

There are so many @kentuckyproud farms to visit this harvest season. Whether your taking home pumpkins, apples, cider donuts, or other farm favorites, you’ll be sure to find the farm that’s just right for you! 

When you support a local farm, you’re supporting local families & your community 💛

Don’t Miss This Holiday Classic!! ❄️🎄

@thelextheatreco is bringing one of my favorite Christmas movies, Irving Berlin’s White Christmas, LIVE right here in Lexington, Kentucky THIS WEEKEND ONLY! ✨

You’ll be transported to 1954, Pine Tree, Vermont as our war heroes Bob Wallace & Phil Davis attempt to give their General a true Christmas miracle full of music, dancing, and of course SNOW!! ❄️ 

The Lexington Theatre Company has put together show stopping cast, music, and sets (I can’t get over the incredible sets!) that are sure to create holiday memories you’ll cherish for years to come! 

There’s no need to fly to NYC this holiday season when The Lexington Theatre Company brings Broadway quality musicals right here to the Bluegrass! 

If you haven’t already, get your tickets before the sell out for any of this weekend’s shows! Link in my bio 🎟️

Friday Nov. 17 at 7:30pm
Saturday Nov. 18 at 1:00pm & 7:30pm 
Sunday Nov. 19 at 1:00pm & 6:30pm

We went to see him at @hamburgpavilion and you can too! There was even an appearance from the Grinch himself 😉

Saturday December 9th & 16th 10am-2pm 
Sunday December 10th & 17th 12pm-4pm

I can’t be the only one who enjoys Christmas shopping right?! The crisp air, pretty lights and decorations, just walking around The Summit feels magical this time of year and I had the best time checking off my christmas list last week!

Gift a luxurious treatment from @dekalashthesummit for those who love experiences—I can’t wait to go back for my own visit with their helpful and knowledgeable staff soon!
